A very simple tweeting sensor.

To get started:
1) Load an arduino with AnalogToSerial.ino
2) construct the circuit described in AnalogToSerial.ino
3) plug in the arduino (and find the port
4) Fill in the following:
    A) port address (of arduino)
    B) twitter info: consumer_key, consumer_secret,
        access_token, access_token_secret
5) run the script


-- Twitter --

For information on the various twitter keys and secrets look at:

http://dev.twitter.com
http://hueniverse.com/oauth/

In brief, you'll need to create an application to get the consumer
key and secret and generate a READ/WRITE access token.


-- Windows --

If this is running on a windows machine, consider using portable python:

http://www.portablepython.com/

Keep in mind, on windows, pythonw.exe does not execute a console.
Take a look at run.bat for an example run script.


-- Debugging --

remove main.py line 4 to make the script less 'chatty'
